verses.roman:
teṅho kahe,--"ye kahilā vidyānagare
sei kathā krame tumi kahibā āmāre

synonyms: teṅho kahe—he replied; ye—what; kahilā—you spoke; vidyā-nagare—at Vidyānagara; sei kathā—those topics; krame—according to the order; tumi—you; kahibā—please speak; āmāre—to me.
translation: Pradyumna Miśra replied, "Kindly tell me about the same topics you spoke about at Vidyānagara.
